# What is Artificial Intelligence (AI)?

Artificial Intelligence (AI) is the ability of machines or computers to perform tasks that normally require human intelligence.
These tasks include learning, reasoning, problem-solving, decision-making, and understanding language.
AI systems analyze data, recognize patterns, and make predictions or decisions.
Examples of AI include virtual assistants, recommendation systems, chatbots, and self-driving cars.
AI helps automate tasks and improve efficiency in many fields.
Generative AI is a subset of AI that focuses on creating new content.








